  <description><![CDATA[<p>If you’re looking for an active holiday Hotel Špik is the perfect place to base yourself. Located around five kilometres outside <a data-udi="umb://document/9b6cf6eac79541f5850e141e41a071ab" href="/{localLink:umb://document/9b6cf6eac79541f5850e141e41a071ab}" title="Kranjska Gora">Kranjska Gora</a> in the village of Gozd Martuljek, it's a great starting point for many impressive walks. The route into Kranjska Gora is a pleasant one along the river - it takes just over an hour to walk or you can hop on the bus.</p>
<h2>Family-friendly facilities and a great spa</h2>
<p>The striking design of the hotel will capture your attention, and the facilities will draw you in – indoor pools and top-class spa facilities are great for a spot of relaxation, or ramp up the action on the outdoor sports courts. There are great children’s facilities here, too.</p>
<p>Inside, there are two accommodation wings, one three-star and one four-star. Three-star rooms are simply furnished and comfortable while the four-star rooms are something a little special. They either face the forest, with a quiet, shaded balcony, or you can opt to look out on the Julian Alps, with a balcony that captures the sun.</p>]]></description>
