  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Three-star double rooms</strong><span> are around 20m² with a balcony and can sleep two people. Some of these rooms have a single sofa bed meaning they can sleep three (if the room is only booked for two people, there won't be a sofa bed in the room). These rooms are available for sole occupancy on a request basis (supplement applies) - please call us to book.</span><span> </span></p>
<p><strong>Forest view four-star double rooms </strong><span>are around 30m² and can sleep two people. These rooms have a balcony with forest views, normally shaded throughout the day. </span></p>
<p><strong>Mountain view four-star double rooms</strong><span> are around 30m² and can sleep two to three people (the extra bed is a single sofa bed). These rooms have mountain views and a balcony that catches the sun.</span></p>
<p><span>Rooms in the four-star part of the hotel have air conditioning.</span></p>
<p><span><strong>All rooms have:</strong> </span></p>
<ul>
<li><span>TV</span></li>
<li><span>Minibar</span></li>
<li>Bath or shower</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>General information</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Check-in: 2 pm</li>
<li>Check-out: 11 am</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Local fees &amp; taxes</strong></p>
<p>A local tourist tax of approx. €3.50 per person per night is payable locally (children aged 7-18 pay a reduced rate of approx. €1.75 per night and children aged 6 and under are exempt).</p>
<p><strong>Accessibility</strong><span></span></p>
<p><span>The hotel has some adapted rooms available. Please call us to book.</span></p>
<ul>
<li><span>Steps into property: <strong>Yes</strong></span></li>
</ul>]]></roomsDescription>
